==English==

===Etymology===
{{confix|gyro|scope|lang=en}}, from {{etyl|fr|en}} coined in 1856 by physicist [[w:Leon Foucault|Leon Foucault]], from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|γῦρος||tr=guros|circle|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}} and {{term|σκοπός||tr=skopos|watcher|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# an apparatus composed of a wheel which spins inside of a frame ([[gimbal]]) and causes the balancing of the frame in any direction or position. In the form of a [[gyroscopic stabilizer]], used to help keep aircraft and ships steady.

